@startuml DailyProblemClassification_DatabaseFlow
title Daily Problem Classification - Database Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam databaseBackgroundColor #E8F5E9
skinparam databaseBorderColor #4CAF50
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #E3F2FD
skinparam activityBorderColor #1976D2

|DataAccess Layer|
start

:GetPADailyScanFromQueue();
|CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)|
:Execute SP: **CTS_DC_CustClassification_DailyScanPA_GetFromQueue**;
note right
  **Database**: CTS_DataCenter.ctsService
  **Timeout**: 300 seconds (default)
  
  **Purpose**: Get PA customers from Daily Scan Queue
  **Queue Source**: Populated by RealtimeClassification
  
  **Returns**:
  - CustID (long)
  - DWSportType (int) - Sport Group
  
  **Logic**:
  - SELECT TOP 10000 FROM CTSCustomerClassification_DailyPAQueue
  - ORDER BY InsertedTime ASC (FIFO)
  - Get oldest PA customers first
end note

:Return PADailyScanFromQueueEntity[];
|Service Layer|
:Store PADailyScanFromQueueModel;

|Service Layer|
:GetProblemAccountLosingClassification();
|bodb_VR2Model (SQL Server)|
:Execute SP: **CTS_ProblemAccountsClassification_Daily**;
note right
  **Database**: bodb_VR2Model.wsv_cts
  **Timeout**: 1200 seconds (20 minutes)
  
  **Purpose**: Calculate Problem Account Losing Classification
  **Input**: CustID list from queue
  
  **Returns**: ProblemAccountLosingClassificationEntity[]
  - CustID
  - CategoryID (PA/PotentialPA)
  - TurnoverRM (betting volume)
  - WinlossRM (loss amount)
  - BetCount (number of bets)
  - ActiveDays (betting frequency)
  - PerformanceTime (calculation period)
  
  **Calculation Logic**:
  1. Get customer betting data
  2. Calculate losing performance:
     - Total turnover
     - Total winloss (negative = loss)
     - Total bet count
     - Active betting days
  3. Apply PA thresholds:
     - High loss amount → PA
     - Medium loss → PotentialPA
  4. Determine PA category based on:
     - Loss amount thresholds
     - Turnover thresholds
     - Activity frequency
     - Performance period
  5. Return classification results
end note

:Return ProblemAccountLosingClassificationEntity[];
|Service Layer|
:Chunk by batchSize;

repeat
  :Reset for batch;
  
  |DataAccess Layer|
  :InsertProblemProbationClassification(JSON);
  |CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)|
  :Execute SP: **CTS_DC_CustClassification_ProblemAccountProbation_Insert**;
  note right
    **Database**: CTS_DataCenter.ctsServiceAdmin
    **Timeout**: 300 seconds (default)
    
    **Purpose**: Insert PA Probation Classification
    **Input**: @ip_ProblemAccount (JSON)
    
    **JSON Structure**:
    {
      "CustID": long,
      "CategoryID": int,
      "TurnoverRM": decimal,
      "WinlossRM": decimal,
      "BetCount": long,
      "ActiveDays": int,
      ...
    }
    
    **Returns**: InsertPAProbationResult[]
    - CTSCustID (long)
    - CustID (long)
    - IsRobot (bool) - Robot detection flag
    
    **Insert Logic**:
    1. Parse JSON PA data
    2. For each PA customer:
       a. INSERT/UPDATE CTSCustomerClassification
       b. Set CategoryID (PA/PotentialPA)
       c. Set CategoryName
       d. Set probation period
       e. Set RelevantCategoryID
       f. Detect if Robot (IsRobot flag)
    3. Return inserted records with Robot flag
    
    **Robot Detection**:
    - Based on betting patterns
    - High frequency + high volume
    - Suspicious activity markers
    - Returns IsRobot = true/false
  end note

  :Return InsertPAProbationResult[];
  |Service Layer|
  :Store problemAccounts (CTSCustID, CustID, IsRobot);
  
  :Filter PA vs Robot (by IsRobot flag);
  
  fork
    |Service Layer|
    :InsertPALogics (Regular PA);
    |Various DBs|
    :Execute PA Logic SPs;
    note right
      **Purpose**: Insert PA detection logic
      **Input**: Regular PA customers (IsRobot = false)
      
      **Logic Types**:
      - PA winning pattern detection
      - PA risk scoring
      - PA behavior analysis
      - PA monitoring rules
      
      **Multiple SPs executed**:
      - Logic insertion
      - Rule configuration
      - Monitoring setup
    end note
  fork again
    |Service Layer|
    :InsertRobotLogics (Robot PA);
    |Various DBs|
    :Execute Robot Logic SPs;
    note right
      **Purpose**: Insert Robot detection logic
      **Input**: Robot PA customers (IsRobot = true)
      
      **Logic Types**:
      - Robot pattern detection
      - Automated betting detection
      - Bot behavior analysis
      - Robot risk scoring
      
      **Separate logic for robots**:
      - Different thresholds
      - Different patterns
      - Stricter monitoring
    end note
  end fork
  
  |Service Layer|
  :PushCCToExternal (CustIDs);
  |External - MainDB|
  :Push Classification to MainDB;
  note right
    **Purpose**: Sync PA classification to MainDB
    **Input**: Distinct CustIDs from problemAccounts
    
    **Parameters**:
    - RoleGroup: Member
    - ExternalBatchSize
    - IsUpdateDangerToMainDB: true
    
    **Process**:
    1. Get classification data by CustID
    2. Format for external system
    3. Push to MainDB API
    4. Update external visibility
    
    **Batching**:
    - Chunk by ExternalBatchSize
    - Parallel push for efficiency
    - Error handling per batch
  end note
  :Return success status;

repeat while (More batches?) is (yes)
-> no;

|DataAccess Layer|
:CompletePADailyScan(custIDs);
|CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)|
:Execute SP: **CTS_DC_CustClassification_DailyScanPA_Complete**;
note right
  **Database**: CTS_DataCenter.ctsServiceAdmin
  **Timeout**: 300 seconds (default)
  
  **Purpose**: Mark PA queue as completed
  **Input**: @CustIDs (comma-separated string)
  
  **Logic**:
  1. Parse CustID list from string
  2. DELETE FROM CTSCustomerClassification_DailyPAQueue
     WHERE CustID IN (parsed list)
  3. Remove processed customers from queue
  
  **Effect**:
  - Clears processed customers from queue
  - Prevents re-processing
  - Enables FIFO for next batch
end note

|Service Layer|
:Check if more customers in queue;
if (More in queue?) then (yes)
  :Return isContinue = true;
  |JobService|
  :Recursive call - JobRun();
  note right
    **Recursive Processing**:
    Continue until queue is empty
  end note
  detach
else (no)
  :Return isContinue = false;
  stop
endif

@enduml

